news.title: Ahmedabad civic body offers 25% tax discount on houses of 40-70 sq metres
news.para: A release from Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation (AMC) said that it has announced this flat discount for 2022-23. The decision was taken in the meeting of the civic body’s standing committee held on Thursday.

news.title: New security firm appointed illegally in Emaar Gurgaon Greens: Residents
news.para: They alleged that he isn’t eligible to become an RWA member as he doesn’t have a valid conveyance deed, which is mandatory for a member. The RWA have also met the police commissioner over the matter.

news.title: Gurugram: Why it's a long struggle ahead for displaced Chintels Paradiso families
news.para: Till a week ago, Vijay Mahanoori (59), a banker, was counting the number of months left for his retirement. After all, he had planned everything for a peaceful retired life — a 3BHK flat at Chintels Paradiso, his daughter’s wedding and so on.

news.title: 'Don't throw us out': NBCC Green View residents in Gurugram are in tears
news.para: Several other families at the Sector 37D society, which has been declare unsafe to live in because of structural damage, were in tears.

news.title: Supertech twin towers: Residents of neighbouring buildings claim lack of information
news.para: Residents in the 130 flats in Aster 2 and 3 and Aspire 1, the Emerald Court buildings that are just a narrow driveway apart from the twin towers, said it’s not so much the actual demolition but the lack of information about how their houses will be secured that has been driving up anxiety levels.

news.title: DTP recommends lodging FIR against Raheja Developers for substandard construction
news.para: "Instructions were given to the management to complete all the works within a time limit. But no satisfactory reply has been given by the builder. Finally, it has been recommended to register a case against Raheja Developers," Sanjay Kumar, DTP (Planning) said.

news.title: Noida authority plans policy to ensure periodical structural audits of buildings
news.para: If approved, the onus will be on the developers and subsequently the apartment owners associations (AOAs) to ensure periodical audits and carry out repairs suggested in the reports.

news.title: SIT issues notice to Chintels India, DTCP to submit papers on Paradiso
news.para: The SIT will go through the documents and then record the statements of the director, architect and Paradiso engineers. So far, two FIRs have been registered in connection with the collapse.

news.title: Chennai: NCLAT sets aside nod for Rs 423 crore Appu Hotels property sale
news.para: M K Rajagopalan, chairman, MGM Healthcare, was the successful bidder in his personal capacity for the properties that include the two Le Royal Meridien Hotels, besides vacant land parcels near Chennai airport.

news.title: Ambuja Cements to invest Rs 3,500 crore for raising cement grinding capacity
news.para: ​"The board has approved in principle an investment of Rs 3,500 crore for a cement grinding expansion plan of potential 7.0 million tonnes across our existing grinding units at Sankrail and Farakka and at a greenfield (fresh) location at Barh, in Bihar," Neeraj Akhoury, MD & CEO of Ambuja Cements.

news.title: Ambuja Cements posts 55.5% dip in net profit to Rs 431 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: Ambuja Cements' total expenses stood at Rs 6,865.61 crore in the December 2021 quarter, a 6.7 per cent jump as compared with Rs 6,434.43 crore a year ago.

news.title: Builders afflicted with low returns, should not list on bourses: Rakesh Jhunjunwala
news.para: It can be noted that very few developers like Macrotech Developers formerly Lodha, and DLF are listed on the bourses. Jhunjunwala cited the case of DLF, saying the stock price plummeted to Rs 80 from Rs 1,300 per piece to illustrate the risks associated.

news.title: Blackstone to buy Preferred Apartment Communities in $5.8 billion deal
news.para: Blackstone Real Estate Income Trust's (BREIT) all-cash offer of $25 per share is nearly 40% higher than Preferred Apartment's stock close on Feb. 9, a day before media reports on the company exploring strategic options including a sale.

news.title: Pune: Broking agency accused of diverting 6.24 crore
news.para: The firm has complained that the manager of the broking agency created a separate account in the name of the realty firm and diverted the money to it without its knowledge.

news.title: Schindler expects China business to contract in 2022 on construction delays
news.para: The Swiss firm expects a "significant" profitability drop of around 20% for the first half of the year, Chief Financial Officer Urs Scheidegger said on a conference call.
